Immediate Support 















Below are a list of 24/7 Hotlines + Chatlines, available for free, confidential support. 
If you are feeling overwhelmed, we suggest calling 2-1-1 to be connected to the national human services center; they provide 24/7 support to connect connect individuals with their needed resources.










PregnancyPlanned Parenthood Hotline 1-800-230-7526 (PLAN) or Text PPNOW to 774636For medical & general pregnancy/women & family health questions.Postpartum Support International Helpline for Pregnant Women, Postpartum Women, Children & Families (24/7)1-800-944-4773 or Text 503-894-9453 (English) or 971-420-0294 (Spanish)This system is available 24/7 and requires you to leave a message, which will be returned as soon as possible. Mental HealthCall 211 for connection with mental/behavioral health services. National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 1-800-273-8255 (TALK) or Text  828255www.suicidepreventionlifeline.orgDisaster Distress Hotline 1-800-985-5990 or Text  TalkWithUs or Hablanos to 828255Peer Emotional Support Line 1-855-845-7415Medical Please call 911 for emergency or crisis medical support. Poison Control (24/7)1-800-222-1222  










Domestic Violence & AbuseThe National Domestic Violence Hotline 1-800-799-7233 (SAFE)www.ndvh.org24/7 Domestic Violence Hotline & Chat 1-866-331-9474 or Text LOVEIS to 22522 or  Chat Nowwww.ndvh.orgNational Child Abuse Hotline/Childhelp 1-800-4-A-CHILD (1-800-422-4453)www.childhelp.orgCrime & Sexual AssaultVictim Connect1-855-484-2845 (VICTIM) or Chat Nowwww.victimconnect.orgNational Human Trafficking Resource Center/Polaris Project Call: 1-888-373-7888 | Text: HELP to BeFree (233733)www.polarisproject.orgNational Sexual Assault Hotline 1-800-656-4673 (HOPE)www.rainn.orgShelter, Housing & FoodCall 211 for crisis housing & food support.Substance AbuseNational Substance Abuse Helpline 1 (800) 662 – 4357 (English & Spanish)www.sahmsa.gov





















 








